# Lifecycle Rules

# create_before_destroy

# Creates the new resource before deleting the old one.

```hcl
lifecycle {

 create_before_destroy = true

}
```

# prevent_destroy

# Prevents accidental deletion.

```hcl
lifecycle {

 prevent_destroy = true

}
```

# ignore_changes

# Ignores changes made outside Terraform.

```hcl
lifecycle {

 ignore_changes = [

   tags

 ]

}
```

---

# Meta Arguments

# depends_on

# Creates explicit dependencies.

```hcl
depends_on = [

 aws_security_group.web

]
```

# count

# Creates multiple resources.

```hcl
count = 3
```

# for_each

# Creates resources from maps or sets.

```hcl
for_each = var.servers
```

Prefer for_each over count.

---

# Senior SRE Golden Rules

# Never apply directly to production.

# Never hardcode secrets.

# Never edit terraform.tfstate manually.

# Never store state locally in production.

# Enable state locking.

# Use reusable modules.

# Avoid Provisioners whenever possible.

# Prefer for_each over count.

# Prefer apply -replace over taint.

# Separate environments.

# Design for High Availability.

# Design for Disaster Recovery.

# Build idempotent infrastructure.

# Automate everything possible.
